<div class="wrap">
    <div class="text-base w-2/3">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-3">Welcome to Smart Calendar Events!</h2>
        <p class="text-lg mb-4">Thank you for installing Smart Calendar Events! This guideline will help you get started with the plugin. Enjoy!</p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-5">
            <li class="mb-2"><strong>Intuitive Event Creation:</strong> Easily create events with a user-friendly interface that allows you to input event details such as title, excerpt, date, image, and description.</li>
            <li><strong>Dynamic Calendar Table Display:</strong> Showcase your events in a visually appealing and organized manner using a dynamic calendar table display. Users can quickly browse through events by date and access event details with ease.</li>
            <li class="mb-2"><strong>Responsive Design:</strong> Ensure a seamless user experience across devices with a responsive design that adapts to various screen sizes, including desktops, tablets, and smartphones.</li>
            <li class="mb-2">
                <strong>Integration with Website:</strong> The <code>[smart-calendar-events]</code> shortcode is a powerful tool for integrating event listings and details into your website's front end. Here's a breakdown of the attributes you can use with this shortcode:
                <ul class="list-decimal pl-5">
                    <li class="my-2"><strong>post-per-page: </strong>This attribute specifies the number of events to display per page. For example, if you set <code>post-per-page="6"</code>, the shortcode will display 6 events per page. You can adjust this number based on your preferences and layout requirements.</li>
                    <li class="mb-2"><strong>order: </strong>This attribute determines the order in which events are displayed. For example, if you set <code>order="ASC/DESC"</code></li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li class="mb-2"><strong>Multilingual Support:</strong> Reach a global audience with multilingual support that allows you to translate event details and interface elements into multiple languages.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
</div>